<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_kadæg" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>kadæg</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>kadængæ</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>эпическая песня</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>epic song</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сказание</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>legend</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сага</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>saga</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>былина</q></cit></sense></sense><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>Narty kadǵytæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Нартовские сказания</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the Nart sagas</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Dareʒanty kadǵytæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Даредзановские сказания</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the Daredzan legends</q></cit></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>jæ xorz kadǵytæn kæron kæm wydi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>его славным былинам не было конца</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there was no end to his glorious epics</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>bakom... mæ fydælty kadæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>прими сказание моих предков</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>accept the legend of my ancestors</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>131</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Narty Wyryzmæǵy kadæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сага о Нарте Урузмаге</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the saga about Nart Uruzmag</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Sanaspi — kadæggænag</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Дзанаспи мастер исполнять былины</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Zanaspi is a master at performing epics</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>86</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>Narty kadǵytæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Нартовские сказания</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the Nart sagas</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Dareʒanty kadǵytæ</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Даредзановские сказания</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the Daredzan legends</q></cit></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>jæ xorz kadǵytæn kæron kæm wydi</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>его славным былинам не было конца</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>there was no end to his glorious epics</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>50</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>bakom... mæ fydælty kadæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>прими сказание моих предков</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>accept the legend of my ancestors</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>131</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Narty Wyryzmæǵy kadæg</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>сага о Нарте Урузмаге</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>the saga about Nart Uruzmag</q></cit></cit><cit type="example"><quote>Sanaspi — kadæggænag</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>Дзанаспи мастер исполнять былины</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>Zanaspi is a master at performing epics</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>86</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Вероятно, производное от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kad"/> ‘слава’ (в смысле „хвалебная песня“), как полагал еще А. %sШифнер%s (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОТ"/><biblScope>51</biblScope></bibl>). По типу образования (прош. причастие + %i-æg%i) ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cadæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/> и др. Вставка %in%i в дигорском — вторичная, как в <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wasængæ"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ǧarængæ"/> и др. Нет основания считать %ikadæg%i заимствованным грузинским %ikadagi%i ‘проповедник’, ‘прорицатель’, вопреки Штакельбергу (<bibl><ref target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl>) и Вс. Миллеру (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl>). Грузинское слово само представляется усвоенным либо из осетинского, либо из пехл. %ikēdig%i ‘magician’ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 84, 91</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОТ"/><biblScope>51</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>68, 86</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">Probably it is a derivative of <ref type="xr" target="#entry_kad"/> ‘glory’(in the meaning „song of praise“), as A. %sSchiffner%s supposed (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОТ"/><biblScope>51</biblScope></bibl>). As for the derivation type (a past participle + %i-æg%i) cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cadæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_syǧdæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_lystæg"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_cærdæg"/> etc. The insertion of %in%i in Digor is secondary, as in <ref type="xr" target="#entry_wasængæ"/>, <ref type="xr" target="#entry_ǧarængæ"/> etc. There is no reason to think that %ikadæg%i is a borrowed Georgian word %ikadagi%i ‘preacher’, ‘prophet’, contrary to Shtakelberg (<bibl><ref target="#ref_MSt."/><biblScope>82</biblScope></bibl>) and Ws. Miller (<bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>10</biblScope></bibl>). It seems that the Georgian word itself was borrowed either from Ossetic, or from Pahlavi %ikēdig%i ‘magician’ (<bibl><ref target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>IX 84, 91</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОТ"/><biblScope>51</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>68, 86</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>